Bayelsa State Police Command has arrested a suspected gunrunner, Victor Ogon, 28, who specialises in fabricating and selling locally-made guns. The police in a statement by command’ spokesman,  Asinim Butswat, said that the suspect was arrested following a tip-off. He said the suspect from Agudama-Epie, Yenagoa, confessed to be a member of Bobos cult group. He stated that the suspect had produced and sold several locally-made guns to cultists and armed robbers in the state. Butswat said detectives are on the trail of some of the cultists who bought locally-made arms from him.